  "idea": "Split useTimelineData.ts (678 LOC) \u2014 the last god hook in the video editor. It mixes 6 concerns: (1) Data fetching/queries (timelineQuery, assetRegistryQuery, saveMutation) ~60 lines. (2) Save/sync lifecycle (saveTimeline, scheduleSave, commitData, applyTimelineEdit, applyResolvedConfigEdit, patchRegistry, editSeqRef, savedSeqRef, saveTimer, lastSavedSignature) ~200 lines. (3) Render state (renderStatus, renderProgress, renderLog, renderDirty, renderResult*, useClientRender wiring) ~60 lines. (4) UI preferences (scaleWidth, activeClipTab, assetPanel state, setters) ~50 lines. (5) Derived/memoized data (resolvedConfig, selectedClip, selectedTrack, compositionSize, renderMetadata, trackScaleMap) ~100 lines. (6) Asset operations (uploadAsset, registerAsset, uploadFiles, invalidateAssetRegistry, resolveAssetUrl, reloadFromServer) ~50 lines. Goal: each concern in its own hook under 200 LOC, useTimelineData becomes a thin orchestrator under 150 LOC that composes them. No behavioral changes \u2014 pure extraction.",
